[h2 
	" Dialog and event script tricks
	$LF
	[a id=heading-5499 
	]a
]h2
[h3 
	" Dialog and event skip
	$LF
	[a id=heading-5534 
	]a
]h3
[h4 
	" Skipping intros with a button combination
	$LF
	[a id=heading-5559 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"For some reason, you can quickly skip all intro screens before the title screen with the start button in Japan versions of all MMZ games, while you can't do the same thing in other versions. Anyhow, you can use a game restart sequence (A+B+Start+Select) at the first logo screen (MMZ1-3) or the second one (MMZ4) to skip to the title screen.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[em 
		(__wikiLink|/TODO|TODO)
		": Exact frames.
	]em
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Skipping boss fights, but being unable to complete the game (MMZ1)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-5974 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"In Neo Arcadia Shrine, you can jump up the roofs of all of the "temples" and skip everything including the bosses inside them. If you skip any boss fight this way, all of the later bosses will disappear from their rooms, because the scripts of entering the fights will not be triggered. You can keep going onto Neo Arcadia Tower and meet Ciel
	[a id=r1 
	]a
	[sup 
		"[
		[a href=#1 
			"1
		]a
		"]
	]sup
	", but you cannot save the game with her. This glitched journey ends in the room right after Ciel, as none of its exits will open once you have entered it.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"[
	[a id=1 
	]a
	[a href=#r1 
		"1
	]a
	"]
	" If you are playing the USA version of MMZ1, Ciel's dialogue will now be in Japanese. (
	[em 
		"TODO: What happens in the Japanese version?
	]em
	")
	$LF
]p
