[h3 
	" Useless but funny glitches
	$LF
	[a id=heading-6801 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"Although currently not useful in a speedrun, these glitches may lead to some new tricks or exploits in future.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Touching spikes without being damaged or dying
	$LF
	[a id=heading-6943 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"When you stand close enough to vertically stretching spikes, you can dash into them and get repelled without being damaged or dying.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Getting killed counterintuitively
	$LF
	[a id=heading-7127 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"Thanks to how detection of collision works, Zero may enter corners unintentionally, and even gets killed being stuck in them for too long (
	[em 
		"TODO: how long?
	]em
	"). This is likely to happen under certain situations:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" When Zero dashes through a very narrow gap that is broadening, which is formed with a stational block and a moving one e.g. an elevator. Such death is counterintuitive because Zero is not crushed, but gets killed in the opposite way.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[em 
		(__wikiLink|/TODO|TODO)
		": More of such things?
	]em
	$LF
